If you look at some of our recent products
that we've launched everything from, you know,

00:00:08.929 --> 00:00:13.799
Google Earth on the Moon to now Google Earth
on the Ocean, we have a really big focus on

00:00:13.799 --> 00:00:18.210
exploration and making information accessible
to everyone.

00:00:18.210 --> 00:00:21.330
And this tradition in the oceans, really you
know got its start

00:00:21.330 --> 00:00:26.210
and got its major push with Jacques Cousteau,
the famous ocean explorer.

00:00:26.210 --> 00:00:29.619
In fact, if you make a visit by the Googleplex
right now we have

00:00:29.619 --> 00:00:32.870
a temporary loan of a sculpture of Jacques
Cousteau

00:00:32.870 --> 00:00:40.899
along with other ocean -- ocean pioneers.
And so, you know, we have a firm connection

00:00:40.899 --> 00:00:44.850
with the sea.
And so today our talk is on the man himself,

00:00:44.850 --> 00:00:52.100
on Jacques Cousteau, his life, his family.
We're joined today by Brad Matsen who is a

00:00:52.100 --> 00:00:54.820
famed ocean author,
and he'll be speaking to us about his latest

